              <div class="grid_8">
                    <h1>Welcome To Shifnal Golf Club</h1>
   
                    <!--<p>Shifnal Golf Club is situated in the beautiful countryside of Shropshire with easy access from the M6 and M54. The outstanding Georgian clubhouse and fine parkland course make it one of the regions leading venues for society and corporate golf and private functions.</p> -->
                <h3>Our Golf Course</h3>
<p>The well manicured course measures 6468 yards (par 71) and 5664 yards (par 72) respectively for men and ladies.  This stunning course has something to offer for golfers of all levels of ability.  We have successfully hosted national and regional events including the English Womens Senior Championship (2012) and the English mid-amateur men's open championship (2008)</p>
 <h3>Our Clubhouse</h3>
 <p>Decker Hill stands as one of Shropshire’s architectural mysteries. A handsome classical Regency house, with a distinguished provenance in terms of ownership, the mansion is today the busy clubhouse for Shifnal Golf Club – whose home it has been since 1964. . . <a href="SGC-History.html">The History of Our Clubhouse Here</a></p>
  <h3>Our Members</h3>
<p>Members of Shifnal Golf Club are part of an inspiring, active and loyal community. As well as a great golf course members have SO MUCH to do and take part in within this community. Competitions most weekends, social events every month, a vibrant bar and a refined restaurant. No matter your age, your gender or your golf ability (you dont even have to play golf) there is something for you to take part in or enjoy at all times. </p>
 <h3>Our Visitors</h3>
<p>Shifnal Golf Club is a private members club which extends a warm welcome to individual visitors and golf societies alike. We pride ourselves on service and quality both on and off the course. We have facilities to host social events and private parties as well as charity and corporate golf days. </p>


                    
